# FunkMaker3000 Workstation Evolution Plan

## 1. Core Architecture: The Three-Tab System
To accommodate the new timeline and recording features, the UI will be refactored into a tabbed workstation layout.

- **TAB 1: TWEAK (The Synth)**
  - Current FunkMaker 3000 interface.
  - Focus: Sound design, oscillator tweaking, and global envelope settings.
  - Action: "Snapshot" the current sound to be used in recordings.

- **TAB 2: LOOP (The Recorder)**
  - Logic: Collapses/hides oscillator rows to show a focused 1-4 measure grid.
  - Performance: Captures live keyboard events (MIDI-style) with high-precision timestamps.
  - **The Snap Logic:** Blocks are created on 1-measure boundaries, but note starts/ends are preserved exactly as played (non-quantized).
  - **Cropping:** Any note held past the recording duration is cropped to fit the block.

- **TAB 3: SONG (The Timeline)**
  - A multi-track horizontal arrangement view.
  - Drag-and-drop saved loops onto the timeline.
  - Snaps to measures for easy structural building.

---

## 2. The Data Bundle (.funk)
Every "Loop" created in FunkMaker will be a JSON object containing:
- **Synth DNA:** A snapshot of all 30+ slider values at the time of recording.
- **Performance Data:** An array of note events (pitch, start time, duration).
- **Metadata:** Name (e.g., "Bass Slap 01"), Color, and Track ID.

> [!NOTE]
> This ensures that when the timeline plays back different blocks, the Synth UI can "jump" to the correct settings for that specific sound.

---

## 3. The "Trashy-Chic" Mic Integration
Low-resolution vocal capture for "Vocal Pads."

- **Technical Specs:**
  - **Codec:** Opus (via MediaRecorder API).
  - **Bitrate:** 12 - 24 kbps (Mono).
  - **Aesthetic:** "Sampleresque" quality (low-fi, telephonic).
- **Storage:** Saved as Base64 strings with `MEDIA_STAMP` for Supabase compatibility.
- **Goal:** Keep 30-60 second clips well under the 1MB per-file limit.

---

## 4. Implementation Stages

### Phase 1: Navigation & State
- Implement the Tab bar across the top of the FunkMaker window.
- Create the "Active Sound Snapshot" system to track the current synth state.

### Phase 2: The Loop Recorder
- Build the "Live Capture" engine.
- Implement the "Metronome" and "Count-in" logic.
- Basic save/load for `.funk` loop bundles.

### Phase 3: The Timeline (Song)
- Multi-track horizontal layout.
- Measure-snapping drag/drop engine.
- Global playback clock to trigger the loops in sync.

### Phase 4: Vocal Pads
- Browser permission request for Microphone.
- Simple "Record" button on a dedicated Mic track.
- Compression/Downsampling pipeline.

---

## 5. Scope & Out-Of-Scope

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **IN SCOPE**
> - Measure-snapped timeline arrangement.
> - Non-quantized note performance data.
> - Synth parameter snapshots per loop.
> - Low-res audio recording (Mic).
> - Simple note cropping at block boundaries.

> [!WARNING]
> **OUT OF SCOPE (For Now)**
> - **Automated Slider Grooves:** Capturing slider movements over time.
> - **Pulsing UI:** Global CSS animations tied to BPM.
> - **Cross-Fades:** Audio blending between blocks.
> - **Infinite Tail:** Preservation of release tails beyond block boundaries.

---

## 6. Storage & Performance
- **Note Data:** Negligible impact on DB limit (~100 bytes per 16-note loop).
- **Vocal Data:** High compression ensures even a 5-minute song with several vocal clips fits within a single 1MB Supabase record.
- **UI Performance:** Tabs will "hibernate" inactive views to prevent DOM lag (e.g., hiding 30+ sliders while in Timeline mode).
